      <h2>Introduction to Figure of Merit</h2>
      <p>
        Earlier, we learned that the deflection of the galvanometer is proportional to the current flowing through it. 
        We can use a formula to represent this relationship:
      </p>

      <i class="i-k">I = kθ</i>

      <div class="in-this-formula-container">
        <span>In this formula, </span><i class="i">I</i><span> represents the current flowing through the galvanometer, and </span>
        <i class="i">θ (theta)</i><span> represents the deflection of the galvanometer.</span>
      </div>

